The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | 10 Indians make shortlist
                                                                                                                       7                                      10 Indians make shortlist
  - ICC Awards Sachin, Sehwag and Dhoni each nominated in three categories       A STAFF REPORTER                            
	Calcutta: India captain Mahendra Singh, Sachin Tendulkar and Virender Sehwag have been nominated in the three main categories for the upcoming LG ICC awards, scheduled to be held in Bangalore, on October 6.         
	The Indian trio have been nominated in the Cricketer of the Year, Test Player of the Year and ODI Player of the Year categories, respectively.         
	The other Indians who have been nominated are youngsters Virat Kohli, Pragyan Ojha and Ravindra Jadeja in the Emerging Player of the Year category. Middle-order batsman Suresh Raina has been nominated in the Best T20 Performance of the Season category.         
	Raina struck a brilliant century against South Africa during the ICC World T20 last May.         
	Indian womens team captain Jhulan Goswami, former captain Mithali Raj and spinner Gouher Sultana have been nominated in the Womens Cricketer of the Year category.         
	Some of the other cricketers who have got nominated in three categories are Hashim Amla and Jacques Kallis of South Africa, Shane Watson and Doug Bollinger from Australia and Sri Lankas Mahela Jayawardene.         
	The ICC awards are an opportunity for the ICC and FICA to acknowledge and celebrate the remarkable performances of the worlds top players, said ICC Chief Executive Haroon Lorgat.         
	It is also a chance for followers of our great sport to reflect on some of the great cricketing feats they have witnessed over the past year. This will be the seventh time the awards have been handed out and picking the winners will not be an easy task for the voting academy, he said.                                                                                                                     
